{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ff12af57-c3a4-4136-b31e-8d4b8c00ea24","content":"With **MSTest 3.8.2**, the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **`TestContext`** — inject via **constructor** (property injection is legacy)\n2. **Sync init** — use `[TestInitialize]`\n3. **Async init** — `[TestInitialize]` supports `async Task` return\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext (MSTest v3+)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task Setup()\n    {\n        // Sync work\n        // ...\n\n        // Async work\n        await SomeAsyncSetupAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        // ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- The old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern still works but constructor injection is preferred in v3+.\n- `[TestInitialize]` can return `void` (sync) or `Task` (async) — no need for separate mechanisms.\n- For one-time class-level async setup, use `[ClassInitialize]` with `async Task` as well.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"20aefd60-3fe4-4251-9d3c-88f349aa6a2a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach has changed significantly. Let me provide the current best practices.\n\nIn MSTest v3+:\n- `TestContext` is injected via constructor (no more `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern)\n- You can implement `IAsyncInitialization` or use `[TestInitialize]` for async init\n- Actually, let me think about this more carefully.\n\nIn MSTest 3.x:\n1. **TestContext injection**: The modern way is constructor injection: `public MyTestClass(TestContext testContext)`\n\n\n2. **Synchronous init**: `[TestInitialize]` method\n3. **Async init**: `[TestInitialize]` can be async (returns `Task`)\n\nFor MSTest 3.4+, `TestContext` is available through constructor injection. The `[TestInitialize]` attribute now supports async methods that return `Task`, and `[ClassInitialize]` handles one-time class-level setup.\n\nFor cleanup, I can implement `IDisposable` or `IAsyncDisposable` depending on whether the test class needs synchronous or asynchronous resource cleanup.","outputTokens":681,"requestId":"4810:2AD648:874E2E:9BAB4A:69FBEB06"},"id":"e4cf21e7-a015-4af4-9195-b182c97d293c","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:29:56.387Z","parentId":"1f59ebfa-9c2b-42cd-86ca-c9e78ba04ffd"}
